## Tuples and Sets
**Tuples** are immutable (can't be changed) ordered collections.
**Sets** are unordered collections of unique elements.

```python
# Tuple
coords = (10, 20)
x, y = coords  # Unpacking
# coords[0] = 5  # ERROR! Tuples are immutable

# Set
unique = {1, 2, 3, 2, 1}  # {1, 2, 3}
unique.add(4)
unique.discard(2)
print(unique)  # {1, 3, 4}

# Set operations
a = {1, 2, 3}
b = {2, 3, 4}
print(a & b)  # Intersection: {2, 3}
print(a | b)  # Union: {1, 2, 3, 4}
```

